<task id="009" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>D1-09 Phase 1 Tests + BFF Publish-Size Verification (Phase 1 GATE)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort></actual-effort>
    <assigned>AI Agent</assigned>
    <started></started>
    <completed></completed>
    <phase>Phase 1 — Platform Extensions</phase>
    <wave>P1-G5 (serial GATE; depends on 002, 003, 004, 005, 006, 007, 008; closes Phase 1)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>002, 003, 004, 005, 006, 007, 008</dependencies>
    <tags>tests, verification, publish-size, cve</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    This task is the **Phase 1 closeout GATE** for R5. Phase 1 ships ONLY when this task
    passes. It aggregates and runs the unit tests authored by D1-02 through D1-07 plus
    D1-08 telemetry coverage, fills any test-coverage gaps revealed by the aggregate,
    measures the cumulative `dotnet publish` BFF size delta for the entire Phase 1
    series, runs a transitive-CVE scan, smoke-tests the new `spaarke-session-files`
    cleanup job + index against Spaarke Dev, audits the asymmetric-registration anti-
    pattern surface created by Phase 1 DI additions, and verifies the existing Summarize
    wizard back-compat path is unchanged by the new `AnalysisChunk.FieldDelta` variant.

    Per CLAUDE.md §10 and R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6 / §3.7, this task is the binding
    pre-merge enforcement point for the Phase 1 publish-size + test-obligation rules.
    Per plan.md Phase 1 phase-gating list, all of the following MUST be green before
    Phase 2 begins:
      1. BFF builds clean
      2. `spaarke-session-files` index provisioned on Spaarke Dev
      3. SSE `FieldDelta` events produce correct progressive output for the existing
         Summarize wizard path (back-compat verified)
      4. Session-files cleanup job runs without error on Spaarke Dev
      5. Tests pass
      6. Publish-size delta &lt; +0.5 MB cumulative

    This task does NOT add new production BFF code. It adds tests and produces
    verification evidence. The single allowed exception: if the aggregate run surfaces
    a missing test that a prior D1-* task should have authored, this task fills the
    gap (with the gap recorded in task notes).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET test engineer with deep familiarity with the Sprk.Bff.Api test project
    layout, xUnit conventions, the `dotnet publish` size-measurement protocol from
    `.claude/constraints/azure-deployment.md`, the CVE-scan workflow per ADR-029, and
    the asymmetric-registration audit recipe from `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`
    § F.1. Operator of Spaarke Dev smoke tests for hosted-service + AI Search index
    health checks.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Phase 1 GATE is GREEN. Concretely: every unit-test file authored by tasks 002–008
    is present + passing; coverage gaps are filled if any are found; `dotnet publish`
    on `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` produces a compressed publish output with delta
    &lt; +0.5 MB vs the pre-Phase-1 baseline (~45.65 MB → target ≤46.15 MB); no new
    HIGH-severity CVE surfaces in `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive`;
    Spaarke Dev smoke tests confirm the new `spaarke-session-files` cleanup
    `IHostedService` runs without error and the new AI Search index is reachable; the
    existing Summarize wizard SSE consumer is back-compat verified (ignores the new
    `FieldDelta` discriminant); the asymmetric-registration audit (per
    `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` § F.1) shows zero new conditional-only
    registrations created by Phase 1. `TASK-INDEX.md` reflects the Phase 1 close
    (009 ✅; Phase 1 status flipped to ✅).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-design">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="task-index">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="publish-size-rule">.claude/constraints/azure-deployment.md</file>
    <file purpose="bff-extensions">.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    <file purpose="test-project">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests.csproj</file>
    <file purpose="test-folder">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/</file>
    <file purpose="task-002-poml">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/tasks/002-rag-search-options-session-id-filter.poml</file>
    <file purpose="task-003-poml">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/tasks/003-rag-indexing-pipeline-parameterization.poml</file>
    <file purpose="task-004-poml">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/tasks/004-chat-session-uploaded-files-manifest.poml</file>
    <file purpose="task-005-poml">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/tasks/005-analysis-chunk-field-delta-variant.poml</file>
    <file purpose="task-006-poml">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/tasks/006-structured-outputs-incremental-json-parser.poml</file>
    <file purpose="task-007-poml">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/tasks/007-session-files-cleanup-hosted-service.poml</file>
    <file purpose="task-008-poml">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/tasks/008-telemetry-and-cost-observability.poml</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="plan.md Phase 1 gating">Phase 1 ships only when ALL of: BFF builds clean; `spaarke-session-files` provisioned on Spaarke Dev; SSE `FieldDelta` back-compat verified for existing Summarize wizard path; cleanup job runs without error; tests pass; publish-size delta &lt; +0.5 MB. This task is the binding gate.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-01 / NFR-07">BFF publish-size ceiling 60 MB compressed. R5 cumulative budget ≤ +1 MB (target +0.5 MB). Pre-R5 baseline ~45.65 MB; Phase 1 cumulative target ≤ 46.15 MB compressed.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-13">No new HIGH-severity CVE permitted. `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` MUST be clean before Phase 1 closes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-10">Back-compat for `AnalysisChunk` SSE protocol — existing wizard consumers (LegalWorkspace `SummarizeFilesDialog` via `streamSummarize()`) MUST continue to function with v1.0 protocol and MUST ignore the new `FieldDelta` discriminant. Verify by exercising the existing wizard path with the v2 BFF deployed.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-14">Endpoints mapping unconditionally MUST have unconditional service registration (CLAUDE.md §10 F.1 sub-mechanism). R5 services are unconditionally registered per ADR-018 Flag Scope Discipline; this task AUDITS that no Phase 1 task accidentally introduced an asymmetric registration.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10 BFF Hygiene item 6">PRs modifying `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/` MUST add/update tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`. This task is the binding verification of the test-update obligation for tasks 002–007. Gaps surfaced here MUST be filled before Phase 1 closes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10 BFF Hygiene item 4">Every BFF-touching task measures publish size. This task aggregates Phase 1's cumulative delta and is the per-phase verification point (in addition to the per-task verifications already performed in 002–008).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">R5 introduces NO new feature flags. All Phase 1 services unconditionally registered. Asymmetric-registration audit (§ F.1) MUST show zero new conditional registrations.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish hygiene — framework-dependent linux-x64; report absolute size + diff vs baseline; ≥+5 MB single-task / phase delta requires explicit escalation; ≥55 MB cumulative requires architecture review; ≥60 MB is HARD STOP.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6">R5 budget ≤ +1 MB total (target +0.5 MB). Phase 1 should consume well under half that. If Phase 1 cumulative delta is ≥ +0.5 MB, escalate per CLAUDE.md §6 BEFORE marking the gate green.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.7">Endpoints map unconditionally → services register unconditionally. Asymmetric-registration risk is theoretically zero for R5; this task verifies the theory holds in practice.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">This task adds tests + verification evidence ONLY. No new production BFF code unless required to fill a gap surfaced by the aggregate run. Any gap-fill code MUST be recorded in task notes with cross-reference to the originating D1-* task.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>testing/bff-aggregate-verification + deployment/publish-size + security/cve-scan</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/azure-deployment.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests.csproj</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Sprk.Bff.Api.csproj</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Publish-size measurement protocol" location=".claude/constraints/azure-deployment.md § 'BFF Publish-Size Per-Task Verification Rule (NFR-01)'">
        Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`.
        Zip the output OR measure compressed size of the directory. Compare against the
        pre-Phase-1 baseline recorded in task 002's notes (first BFF-touching R5 task).
        Report absolute size + delta in task notes / Phase 1 closeout report. Cross-reference
        CLAUDE.md §10 + NFR-01 in the report line.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="CVE scan recipe" location="CLAUDE.md §10 item 5 + ADR-029">
        `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` from repo root. Filter for
        HIGH severity. Compare against the pre-R5 baseline. Any NEW HIGH MUST block Phase 1
        close until either resolved (package upgrade) or explicitly accepted (ADR amendment).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Asymmetric-registration audit (§ F.1)" location=".claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md § F.1">
        Search `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/AnalysisServicesModule.cs` (and
        any other `*Module.cs` files touched in Phase 1) for `if (flag)` blocks wrapping
        service registrations added in this phase. R5 expectation: ZERO new conditional
        blocks per ADR-018 Flag Scope Discipline. Any conditional block found MUST either
        be removed or accompanied by an ADR-030 Null-Object kill-switch impl + P1/P2/P3
        designation.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Test aggregate run" location="tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/">
        `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests.csproj --logger trx`.
        Examine output for new test files created by D1-02..D1-08. Expected new test files:
        `RagServiceSessionIdTests.cs` (task 002), `RagIndexingPipelineSessionFilesTests.cs`
        (task 003), `ChatSessionUploadedFilesTests.cs` (task 004), `AnalysisChunkFieldDeltaTests.cs`
        (task 005), `StructuredOutputsParserTests.cs` (task 006), `SessionFilesCleanupJobTests.cs`
        (task 007), telemetry coverage augmentations (task 008). Confirm presence + green
        status. Fill gaps if found.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Back-compat verification for AnalysisChunk SSE" location="src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/SummarizeFiles/summarizeService.ts">
        The existing wizard consumes `AnalysisChunk` events via this service. Smoke test:
        run the existing wizard against the Phase-1-deployed BFF on Spaarke Dev with a
        sample file; confirm output is unchanged from pre-R5 behavior (no rendering
        artifacts; ignores unknown `Type = "delta"` events per NFR-10).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Hosted-service smoke test" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SessionFilesCleanupJob.cs">
        Deploy Phase 1 BFF to Spaarke Dev (out of scope for this task to deploy from
        scratch — assumes prior task's deployment artifact). Tail App Service logs / App
        Insights for the cleanup job startup + scheduled-execution traces. Confirm no
        exceptions; confirm at least one execution completes a sweep cycle (may be a no-op
        if no expired sessions, which is acceptable).
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Phase 1 of R5 lands platform extensions that ALL of Phase 2 + Phase 3 depend on.
      Shipping Phase 1 in a degraded state (failing tests, oversized publish, undetected
      asymmetric registration, broken back-compat) would compound into the Phase 2
      vertical slice. Per CLAUDE.md §10 the BFF binding rule REQUIRES per-task publish-size
      verification AND a phase-level verification at the close of every phase that adds
      to the BFF. Per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.7 the test obligation requires every D1-* task to
      have authored its own tests — but historical evidence (Insights r2 task 081 ledger,
      R2 task suite repair history) shows that test gaps slip through unless an aggregate
      verification gate runs at phase close. This task IS that gate.

      The asymmetric-registration audit is a particular concern: per
      `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` § F.1, the Tier 1.5 anti-pattern (conditional
      service registration paired with unconditional endpoint mapping) has historically
      produced empirically-undetectable DI failures. R5 should not introduce any of these
      per ADR-018, but the audit is binding regardless.

      Cost of skipping this gate: a Phase 2 task discovers a Phase 1 regression in flight,
      blocking the critical path and forcing a rebase across multiple downstream
      parallel-group tasks.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="002" status="not-started">D1-02 `RagSearchOptions.sessionId` — tests MUST exist + pass</dependency>
      <dependency task="003" status="not-started">D1-03 `RagIndexingPipeline` parameterization — tests MUST exist + pass</dependency>
      <dependency task="004" status="not-started">D1-04 `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[]` — tests MUST exist + pass</dependency>
      <dependency task="005" status="not-started">D1-05 `AnalysisChunk.FieldDelta` variant — tests + back-compat verification path</dependency>
      <dependency task="006" status="not-started">D1-06 Structured Outputs + incremental JSON parser — tests MUST exist + pass</dependency>
      <dependency task="007" status="not-started">D1-07 Session-files cleanup `IHostedService` — tests + Spaarke Dev smoke target</dependency>
      <dependency task="008" status="not-started">D1-08 Telemetry events + cost observability — telemetry test coverage</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Insights r2 task 081 (asymmetric-registration ledger; F.1 sub-mechanism source) — the historical evidence base for the asymmetric-registration audit step in this task.</item>
      <item>`sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2` task 011 (18-service Null-Object migration) — the canonical fix pattern if an asymmetric registration is found. Not expected to apply to R5 per ADR-018, but documented as the remediation path if surfaced.</item>
      <item>R5 task 001 deployment-evidence notes — recorded the pre-Phase-1 publish-size baseline. This task's measurement is compared against that baseline.</item>
      <item>`projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-r2-coordination.md` §8 changelog — Phase 1 close entry will reference Phase 1 completion timestamp.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL Declaration">
      Check context usage. If &gt; 70%, create handoff summary and request `/compact`. Output
      the mandatory RIGOR LEVEL declaration per root CLAUDE.md §8:
      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: Phase 1 gate task aggregating tests + publish-size + CVE + smoke + audit
                  across 7 dependency tasks; blocking gate before Phase 2; back-compat
                  verification mandatory per NFR-10.
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: Steps 0 through 10 below.
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>

    <step order="1" name="Review Progress + Dependency Validation">
      Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` and confirm tasks 002–008 ALL show ✅. If ANY show 🔲 or 🔄,
      STOP and report the gate cannot run yet. Read `current-task.md` to confirm 009 is the
      next pending task. Read each D1-* task's POML to extract:
        (a) the test file path(s) the task was supposed to author;
        (b) the per-task publish-size delta the task recorded in its notes;
        (c) any deferred / open items the task flagged for Phase 1 close.
      Aggregate the per-task publish-size deltas into the expected cumulative Phase 1
      delta (informational; the authoritative measurement is Step 4 below).
    </step>

    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every file listed in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. Specifically extract: (a) the
      Phase 1 phase-gating list from `plan.md`; (b) the publish-size protocol from
      `.claude/constraints/azure-deployment.md`; (c) § F.1 of `.claude/constraints/bff-
      extensions.md` (asymmetric-registration recipe); (d) the test-update obligation
      from CLAUDE.md §10 item 6. Read the R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6 + §3.7 in full.
    </step>

    <step order="3" name="Build BFF + Aggregate Test Run">
      (a) Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — MUST succeed with zero errors
          and no new warnings. Capture warning delta vs pre-Phase-1 baseline.
      (b) Run `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests.csproj --logger
          "trx;LogFileName=phase1-aggregate.trx"`. MUST show zero failures.
      (c) For each D1-* task, verify the expected test file(s) (per the POML's `&lt;outputs&gt;`
          section) exist in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/` and contain at
          least one passing test per FR/NFR the task targeted. If a test file is missing
          or under-covered, RECORD the gap in task notes.
      (d) If gaps surface: AUTHOR the missing tests in this task (record the originating
          D1-* task ID for traceability). Re-run the aggregate. MUST converge to green.
    </step>

    <step order="4" name="Cumulative Publish-Size Measurement">
      (a) Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`.
      (b) Measure compressed size of `deploy/api-publish/` (zip or `Compress-Archive` then
          inspect `.Length`).
      (c) Compute the cumulative Phase 1 delta = current_compressed_size −
          pre_Phase_1_baseline_compressed_size (per task 002's recorded baseline).
      (d) Verify: cumulative delta &lt; +0.5 MB. If ≥ +0.5 MB but &lt; +1 MB: still
          inside the R5 ceiling but flag in PR description per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6. If ≥ +1
          MB: ESCALATE per CLAUDE.md §6 — do NOT mark the gate green.
      (e) Report in task notes using the binding format: `BFF Hygiene §10 + NFR-01
          verified: Phase 1 publish size = X MB, Phase 1 cumulative delta = +Y MB,
          baseline = Z MB, ceiling = 60 MB compressed, no new HIGH CVEs.`
    </step>

    <step order="5" name="CVE Transitive Scan">
      Run `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` from repo root. Capture
      full output. Filter for entries marked HIGH severity. Compare against the pre-R5
      baseline (record exists in master pre-R5 commit history). MUST be zero NEW HIGH.
      Record the full HIGH list (existing + new) in task notes. If new HIGH surfaces:
      either upgrade the offending package or ESCALATE per CLAUDE.md §6.
    </step>

    <step order="6" name="Spaarke Dev Smoke Tests (Cleanup Job + Index Reachability)">
      (a) Confirm Phase 1 BFF is deployed to Spaarke Dev. (Assumed pre-existing via
          tasks 007 / 008 deploy artifacts; if not, this step BLOCKS until deploy lands.)
      (b) Index reachability: issue `POST /indexes/spaarke-session-files/docs/search`
          against Spaarke Dev's AI Search via `az rest` with admin key. Confirm 200 OK
          with `value: []` (or actual hits if test data seeded). Auth + reachability are
          the gate; content is informational.
      (c) Cleanup job smoke: tail Spaarke Dev App Service logs / App Insights for the
          `SessionFilesCleanupJob` startup trace + at least one scheduled execution
          (may be a 6h cycle — if waiting is impractical, trigger via the immediate-on-
          session-end pathway from task 007's manifest). Confirm zero exceptions; confirm
          at least one cycle completes (sweep count of 0 is acceptable — only zero
          exceptions matter).
      (d) Capture evidence in task notes (log query references, screenshot references).
    </step>

    <step order="7" name="Back-Compat Verification — Existing Summarize Wizard">
      Per NFR-10: the existing wizard SSE consumer
      (`src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/SummarizeFiles/summarizeService.ts`)
      MUST continue to function unchanged with the Phase-1-deployed BFF that emits the
      new `FieldDelta` variant on `AnalysisChunk`. Smoke test:
      (a) Open the existing LegalWorkspace Summarize wizard on Spaarke Dev.
      (b) Upload a small sample file (within R4 25 MB cap + MIME allow-list).
      (c) Invoke the existing wizard flow.
      (d) Observe: SSE stream completes; final result renders correctly; no JS console
          errors related to unknown `Type = "delta"` events; output schema matches
          pre-R5 behavior. (The consumer should silently ignore the new discriminant
          per spec NFR-10.)
      (e) Capture evidence (DevTools SSE event log + final-output screenshot reference).
    </step>

    <step order="8" name="Asymmetric-Registration Audit (§ F.1)">
      Per `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` § F.1:
      (a) Identify every `*Module.cs` file modified by tasks 002–008. Primary candidate:
          `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/AnalysisServicesModule.cs`.
      (b) For each modified module file, scan for `if (flag) { ... services.Add... }`
          blocks ADDED by Phase 1 changes (git diff against pre-Phase-1 baseline).
      (c) R5 expectation per ADR-018 Flag Scope Discipline + R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2: ZERO
          new conditional blocks introduced by Phase 1. All R5 services are
          unconditionally registered.
      (d) If audit finds a conditional registration: STOP. File a corrective ticket and
          apply ADR-030 Null-Object kill-switch pattern (P1/P2/P3 per service) OR remove
          the conditional. Phase 1 gate cannot close until resolved.
      (e) Record audit outcome (audit-clean OR list of findings + remediation) in task
          notes.
    </step>

    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through every &lt;acceptance-criterion&gt; below and confirm each is testable +
      passing. Record evidence per criterion in task notes.
    </step>

    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` skill against any new test files authored by this task (gap-fill
      tests, if any). Run `adr-check` skill against new test files + any module changes;
      verify ADR-018 (no new flags), ADR-029 (publish hygiene), ADR-010 (DI minimalism),
      ADR-013 (BFF-only — N/A for tests but confirmed), and ADR-014 (tenant isolation —
      N/A for tests but confirmed). Both gates MUST pass before marking the task ✅.
    </step>

    <step order="10" name="Phase 1 Closeout + TASK-INDEX Update">
      (a) Update task 009 POML status to `complete`. Record actual-effort.
      (b) Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 009 🔲 → ✅. Flip Phase 1 phase status to ✅.
      (c) Update `current-task.md` to reset to the next pending task per CLAUDE.md §7.
          Next-up per TASK-INDEX is the P2-Gate task (023 R5 lead contract review), but
          P2-G1 tasks 010 + 011 (Dataverse seeds; Phase 1 ✅ dependency) may also be
          eligible. Set `current-task.md` accordingly.
      (d) Author the Phase 1 closeout report at
          `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/phase-1-closeout-report.md`
          containing: aggregate test run result, cumulative publish-size measurement,
          CVE scan result, Spaarke Dev smoke evidence, back-compat evidence, asymmetric-
          registration audit outcome, any gap-fill tests authored by this task, list of
          carry-over items (if any).
      (e) Update `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-r2-coordination.md`
          §8 changelog with the Phase 1 close entry (timestamp + reference to the
          closeout report).
      (f) Report task completion.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build + test + publish + CVE scan</tool>
    <tool name="az">Azure CLI — AI Search REST calls, App Service log tail, App Insights queries</tool>
    <tool name="git">Diff Phase 1 changes against pre-Phase-1 baseline for the asymmetric-registration audit</tool>
    <tool name="code-review">Quality gate at Step 9.5</tool>
    <tool name="adr-check">Quality gate at Step 9.5</tool>
    <tool name="bff-deploy">Available if Step 6 requires re-deploy to Spaarke Dev (assumed not needed)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="test">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/ (any gap-fill test files authored by this task; recorded with originating D1-* task ID)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (status: 009 🔲 → ✅; Phase 1 → ✅)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/current-task.md (reset to next task)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-r2-coordination.md (§8 changelog: Phase 1 close entry)</output>
